OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FHow does the vote take place?
OL,7,FOnce the cardinals have arrived, the
OL,8,Fconclave begins with a special morning
OL,9,FMass in St Peter's Basilica. In the
OL,10,Fafternoon, the cardinals walk to the
OL,11,FSistine Chapel to start the voting
OL,12,Fprocess.
OL,14,FThe College of Cardinals then take a
OL,15,Fvow of secrecy inside the chapel, and
OL,16,Fwith the exception of a few workers,
OL,17,Fno one else is allowed in.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
